Package edu.umd.cs.psl.reasoner.function

Provides interfaces and classes for defining functions that Reasoners can interpret.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FunctionSingleton
    A FunctionTerm with at most one FunctionVariable.
    FunctionTerm
    A numeric function.
    FunctionVariable
    A variable in a numeric function.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AtomFunctionVariable
    Encapsulates the value of a GroundAtom for use in numeric functions.
    ConstantAtomFunctionVariable
    Encapsulates the value of a GroundAtom for use in numeric functions.
    ConstantNumber
    A FunctionTerm with constant value.
    ConstraintTerm
    A numeric constraint.
    FunctionSum
    A numeric function defined as a sum of FunctionSummands.
    FunctionSummand

    MaxFunction

    MutableAtomFunctionVariable

    A FunctionTerm raised to the power of two.

    Enum Description
    FunctionComparator

Package edu.umd.cs.psl.reasoner.function Description

Provides interfaces and classes for defining functions that Reasoners can interpret. GroundKernels use these to define their incompatibility and constraint functions.
